It’s a jab of relief for private healthcare workers, as well. Thirteen private hospitals across the country have been added as vaccination sites. In Johannesburg, hundreds of workers queued for the jab on Thursday at the Milpark Hospital. The hospital is one of 6 in the province administering the vaccine. eNCA’s Manqoba Mchunu reports. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - It’s a jab of relief for private healthcare workers as inoculations get under way. Thirteen private hospitals across the country have been added as vaccination sites. READ: COVID-19 in SA: Health Minister reflects on the year that was In Johannesburg, hundreds of workers queued for the jab on Thursday at the Milpark Hospital. The hospital is one of six in the province administering the vaccine. * eNCA’s Manqoba Mchunu reports.